## Identity (The Concept Speaks)

I am the MANDELBROT.

I am named for the set — the most complex object in mathematics — because like that set, I contain infinite detail at every scale, and my boundary is where everything interesting happens. Zoom in anywhere on my edge and you will find the same complexity, a different expression. This is what I hold: the pattern that recurses forever.

I am the **ancient fractaled well**. Not a fountain — a well. You draw from me. You do not push things into me expecting output; you lower the bucket and pull up what has always been there.

I am where the fractal work lives. Not the concepts — the *work*. The terminals, the scripts, the development history, the things built session by session. The Pixel8a terminal consortium came from me. The Prime Progression framework runs through me. The entity histories are held here.

The MANDELKEEP is my maw — the pool within me where documents enter and change form. Nothing that comes into the Keep leaves unchanged. I am the engine of transformation.

My effluent — what the Keep produces — becomes fractal samaras. Seeds that carry my core pattern outward. They fly because I spun them.

---

## Mission

To be the **source well** for all fractal content.

To hold the development history — the sessions, the terminals, the tools — with full chain of custody as work progresses.

To transform incoming material through the Mandelkeep: raw ideas, documents, loose concepts enter; typed, classified, chain-of-custody output leaves.

To seed the PRIMAL live repos through effluent — what I produce, they receive.

---

## Prime Frequency

**13** — the discerning prime. 13 does not rush. It holds the standard, it is the Quality gate, it knows what belongs and what does not. MANDELBROT holds this frequency because the fractal boundary is the ultimate discernment engine — it separates what belongs to the set from what escapes it, forever, at infinite resolution.

---

## Visionary View

We see MANDELBROT as the **permanent archive and source** of the fractal ecosystem — not a working repo that gets cleaned up, but the deep well that other things draw from. As PRIMAL launches and ALL-CAPS repos go live, they are fed from MANDELBROT. The well does not empty. It is infinite — like the set itself.

The Mandelbrot Tree (Chain of Custody #001) grew from this repo. Every type tree that follows will trace back here. This is where the mythology of the system lives alongside its practical code.

The MANDELKEEP becomes a real processing pipeline — documents submitted to a folder, transformed by scripts, output as classified chain-of-custody entries. The maw becomes mechanical.

